ARCHITECTURE.md
     1‚Üí# Architecture
     3‚Üí> Document is a work in progress!
     4‚Üí
     5‚Üí‚åòK is born from a simple constraint: can you write a combobox with filtering and sorting using the [compound component](https://kentcdodds.com/blog/compound-components-with-react-hooks) approach? We didn't want to render items manually from an array:
     6‚Üí
     7‚Üí```tsx
     8‚Üí// No
     9‚Üí<>
    10‚Üí  {items.map((item) => {
    11‚Üí    return <div>{item}</div>
    12‚Üí  })}
    13‚Üí</>
    14‚Üí```
    15‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
    46‚Üí## Approach
    50‚Üí### Discarded approach
    52‚ÜíWe did not use `React.Children` iteration because it will not support component composition. There is no way to "peek inside" the items contained within `<BlogItems />`, so those items cannot be filtered.
    53‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
